Best new restaurant in SD. Get the New York steak, it's very well made for a fish place! The seabass is also good, great sear to it. Love everything we ordered. Manager even came around to talk to us. Very trendy and modern.

Last night we had an unforgettable feast at the new Lionfish restaurant downtown in The Gaslamp Quarter.  This is a swanky, à la mode establishment you do not want to miss out on. Our server, Steven, was extremely knowledgeable, friendly …

The sushi flight is very nice. Rock shrimp is a nice appetizer.  Quality of the ingredients is very good.  The wine list has some unique items and is not the stale list you tend to see downtown.  Overall, there are some interesting items, but nothing blew me away.
The portions are a bit small for the price. But I guess that is what you get with high end restaurants.

Had a very nice time while visiting. All of the food and drinks were spectacular. We had the Swordfish and the pork chop with sides. The chicory and sunchokes are an absolutely must. The dessert was fun too. Service could have been a little faster as our entire dinner was over 2 hours but they kept us entertained.

My date and I had a great meal and fantastic service from the start. Although it went a little down hill towards the end when we were waiting for our entree. But overall for being a new establishment they did a wonderful job hosting us for …

This place is TOP NOTCH! I was wondering when san diego was going to add somewhere that was elegant and current. High class dining. Amazing theme. Elite af staff. The views inside are just as beautiful as the ones looking out. There's just something special about being in a place that spent so much effort making things extravagant.
